task.summary: Default task
Initial Commit
Created fullscreen xml file
Implemented play, next, and prev controller functions using http://stackoverflow.com/a/6362219
Created SongsManager to manage Songs. Fixed up some code in Song and CalmifyFragment.
Implemented method to update UI using playing song's title and artist
Created sample background image. Fixed play/pause buttons. Fixed looping feature of mediaplayer.
Synchronized background image with current song. Created drawable-nodpi folder thanks to http://stackoverflow.com/a/14877627.
Fixed Play/Pause button UI (broke on configuration changes)
Hid status bar for more immersive experience via https://developer.android.com/training/system-ui/status.html
Created gif wallpapers! Used third-party library https://github.com/koral--/android-gif-drawable
Added official music and gifs. Implemented immersive full-screen mode via https://developer.android.com/training/system-ui/immersive.html#nonsticky
1) Created landscape variation for spacing out media controls 2) Made song title easier to read via shadows 3) Added more music and themes
Added "summer day" song
Deleted unnecessary images and gifs

1) Added "Eternity", "Pachabelly", "Angelic Forest" and "It came upon a midnight clear"
2) Fixed lowmemorykiller bug via shadowradius (had it on 30 in landscape layout. Set to 25)
Added the rest of the songs playlist. Total = 13 songs

Imported SlidingMenu library by jfeinstein10 using http://stackoverflow.com/questions/19079072/how-to-import-slidingmenu-on-android-studio
Library: https://github.com/jfeinstein10/SlidingMenu
Removed "Prelude No. 23" for "Canon in D". Deleted unused gifs for memory.
Created ImageManager class to manager image files. Fixed documentation and comments.
Improved MVC framework by creating a "Playback" interface and "PlaybackController" class
Fixed MediaPlayer looping bug. After song was completed, the first song (songIndex = 0) was played.

Adding a navigation menu for selecting a new song.
Sources: https://developer.android.com/training/implementing-navigation/nav-drawer.html https://developer.android.com/reference/android/support/v4/widget/DrawerLayout.html
